</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[648,739,1414,1438]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[648,739,1414,1438]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the thin, tapering RTA (
<figureCitation box="[1051,1128,1414,1438]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="71.[151,250,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[169,1416,199,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@71.[151,1436,193,1870]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURE 39. Geraesta hirta (USNM). A – C male palp (A, C retrolateral, B ventral); D epigynum, ventral view; E vulva, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (D, E), 0.2 mm (A – C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049518/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig 
<number box="[1098,1128,1414,1438]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[1160,1192,1414,1438]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="40.0">40</number>
B). Separated from 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Geraesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mkwawa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">G. mkwawa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[256,345,1450,1474]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[256,345,1450,1474]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the presence of C and longer RTA (
<figureCitation box="[782,869,1450,1474]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="71.[151,250,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[169,1416,199,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@71.[151,1436,193,1870]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURE 39. Geraesta hirta (USNM). A – C male palp (A, C retrolateral, B ventral); D epigynum, ventral view; E vulva, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (D, E), 0.2 mm (A – C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049518/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[839,869,1450,1474]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="39.0">39</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[900,932,1450,1474]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="40.0">40</number>
B). Females can be separated by the short EL (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1486,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 39" captionStartId="71.[151,250,1891,1914]" captionTargetBox="[169,1416,199,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@71.[151,1436,193,1870]" captionTargetPageId="71" captionText="FIGURE 39. Geraesta hirta (USNM). A – C male palp (A, C retrolateral, B ventral); D epigynum, ventral view; E vulva, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm (D, E), 0.2 mm (A – C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1049518/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
